Fig. 3
 shows the X-ray diffraction pattern (XRD) of as-prepared samples by the ball milling-hydrothermal method. The peak related to CQD is not visible in 5%, 10%, and 15% of Z-CQD nanocomposites due to low contents and weak CQD crystallinity. However, in the XRD pattern of of Z-CQD nanocomposite (20%), the peak at 2θ: 21.97 relates to the crystal of carbon quantum dots (Fig. 4
) [31]. Also, peaks (100), (002), (101), (102), (110), (103), (200), (112), (201), (004), and (202) are related to hexagonal crystal structure of pure zinc oxide sheets (JCPDS No. 36–145) [32].
